	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you want to be accurate, the NTSC NES VBlank period is not over 2000 CPU cycles. It's closer to 1886 2/3 cycles. VBlank is 20 scanlines, each scanline takes 283 PPU cycles, and 1 CPU cycle is equal to 3 PPU cycles. So: 
<br />
<br />20*283/3 = 1886.6666...
<br />
<br />I just don't want someone to waste their time coding something that takes 1900 cycles of VBlank and have them go "Why doesn't it work?"

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

